<title>UK: STV confirms Grampian bid talks.</title>
<headline>STV confirms Grampian bid talks.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Scottish Media Group Plc, the owner of Scottish Television, confirmed on Sunday it is in discussions which may lead to an agreed offer for Grampian Television Plc.</p>
<p>In a statement, the companies said Scottish Media's offer was in the region of 320 pence per ordinary Grampian share, compared with Grampian's closing price on Friday of 265 pence.</p>
<p>Representatives of the two companies were not available for comment.</p>
